dmca.title: Infringment of product
dmca.body:
I recently discovered that your company has trademarked/copyrighted the phrase "SYSTEM 10". As you/your clients may not  be aware there is a product, made by me which has the phrase "SYSTEM 10" in its product. Babya System 10 is a shell replacment which is famous because of the many places where you can get it from. This version has been availabvle since April 2002, and it is a popular download. This product was released early last year and it is a successful application.  
 
My work is copyrighted under Australian ciopyright laws, and I personally value the importance of my product's identity and embarrsment to users/clents.

Could you please reply, in a email addressed to babyap2002@yahoo.co.uk, how long have you used the words "SYSTEM 10" for and any copyrigyt guidelines that may be in place. I cannot afford a leghal case, as I'm [young].
